      "rationale": "Eleven constructs were assembled from a single production lot of non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and 5.5 mm Ti rods. Six constructs were tested at Laboratory A and five at Laboratory B, providing inter-laboratory variability data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two distinct load configurations or offset distances per ASTM F1717.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single 40 mm offset distance per ASTM F1717. Although this is the standard configuration, only one offset condition was evaluated, limiting generalizability. Achieved level falls one gradation below required; this gap is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory standard specifies a single configuration."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation boundary conditions and material inputs traceable to the same physical conditions as the bench test.",
      "rationale": "Each simulation was parameterized using measured values from the corresponding physical construct where available (screw geometry, rod diameter, torque). The 40 mm offset, load application point, and fixture constraints in the FEA replicate the ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry confirmed by CAD-to-fixture comparison."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
