    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework demonstrates sufficient credibility for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending COU. All three QoIs satisfy the quantitative acceptance criteria (relative difference <10%, E/uval <1.96). The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 specifies a single offset configuration and regulatory precedent supports this limitation. Overall credibility is assessed as Medium, consistent with the model risk level and decision consequence.",
